            "type": "com.atlassian.jira.issue.fields.CommentSystemField",
            "value": [
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/22303",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=al_the_x",
                        "name": "al_the_x",
                        "displayName": "David Rogers",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Actually, the proposed solution is insufficient to fix this problem as this will still generate an invalid query: \n\n(`field` = NULL) \u2260 (`field` IS NULL) \n\nAt least in MySQL > 5.1.x, I can attest. In our projects we have overridden the WHERE clause builder in Zend_Db_Table_Abstract to produce the correct query strings for set values, such that PHP's NULL value produces SQL's \"IS NULL\" expression, PHP arrays produce SQL \"IN()\" expressions, etc.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=al_the_x",
                        "name": "al_the_x",
                        "displayName": "David Rogers",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2008-06-11T13:35:27.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2008-06-11T13:35:27.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/37112",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=ralph",
                        "name": "ralph",
                        "displayName": "Ralph Schindler",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "I am not sure how we'd go about fixing this, you are making the assumption that the database driver contextually understand what you mean by _quote(null).\r\n\r\nPerhaps this is a \"Won't Fix\"?",
